--
-- v0.2 observations:
--
-- ⊢= aggregate-results demonstrates the ⊢= expression language with v0.2
--   primitives (count, filter, zip, if-then-else). No LLM needed. The hard/soft
--   boundary is clean: fact-checking is soft (requires world knowledge), but
--   aggregating verdicts is pure deterministic computation.
--
-- Guard clauses enable clean dispatch:
--   - rewrite-article fires only when corrections needed (all-pass = false)
--   - final-article fires only on success (all-pass = true)
--   - incomplete-article fires only on failure (all-pass = false)
--   Without guards (R16), rewrite-article ran even when all-pass = true
--   and had to include "if all-pass, output unchanged" logic in its ∴ body.
--   Guards move this dispatch to the deterministic layer.
--
-- Replace mode on ⊢⊢ spawn-fact-checkers is essential: each iteration needs
--   FRESH verdicts on possibly-corrected claims. Accumulating old fact-check
--   cells would mix stale verdicts with current ones. This is the opposite of
--   program 08 (red-team-harden) where regression tests ACCUMULATE — there,
--   old tests must persist to prevent regression. Here, old verdicts are invalid
--   after rewriting.
--
-- Aspirational oracles on generate-article (under ⊢∘) meant the article was
--   frozen immediately despite being ⊢∘-managed. The loop's convergence
--   criterion (all-pass) is the real quality gate, not the cell's own oracles.
